HEADWORD: Quarte
<hw>Quarte</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>quarte</ets>, prop., a fourth. Cf.
<er>Quart</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Fencing)</fld> <def>A position in thrusting
or parrying, with the inside of the hand turned upward and the point of
the weapon toward the adversary's right breast.</def>⟦br⟧
